.TH "bee-download" "1" "2012-08-31" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee - bau et einfach"

.SH "NAME"
bee\-download \- Download a repository and convert it into a source tarball

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee download"
.OP options
.I <repository-url>
.YS

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-download
is used to download a repository and convert it into a source tarball. This tarball can be used to
create a beefile via
.BR "bee init" .

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.BI "\-n, \-\-pkgname" " <name>"
Specifiy the tarballs package name.
.TP
.BI "\-v, \-\-pkgversion" " <version>"
Specifiy the tarballs package version.
.TP
.BI "\-c, \-\-commit" " <rev>"
When downloading from a git repository: Use a certain commit as the HEAD revision.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-type
Specify the type of download (http, https or git).
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a little help screen.

.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_DOWNLOADDIR
.RS
The downloaded file is placed here.

